The product of the two numbers is a multiple of 5 if and only if at least one die shows a 5. The total number of outcomes when rolling two fair 6-sided dice is \(6 \times 6 = 36\). The number of outcomes where neither die shows a 5 is \(5 \times 5 = 25\). Therefore, the number of favorable outcomes is \(36 - 25 = 11\).

The probability is \(\frac{11}{36}\).

\boxed{\frac{11}{36}}

